The United States has strongly condemned the use of violence by Yemeni government forces against demonstrators in Sanaa, Taiz, and Hodeida. The US supports the Yemeni people in their quest for political and economic reform. They call upon the Yemeni government to conduct full investigations into these events and hold those responsible accountable. The US also urges President Ali Abdullah Saleh to resolve the political impasse with the opposition in order to facilitate meaningful political change in a peaceful manner. They call upon all sides to engage in constructive political dialogue and prioritize Yemen's unity, progress, and future prosperity.